title: How has the proportion of people dying in their usual place of residence changed?
analysis_commentary: The proportion of patients dying in their usual place of residence has risen steadily over the course of the time period; increasing from 37.9% of deaths between January and December 2008, to 44.9% of deaths between July 2013 and June 2014.
data_source: National end of life care intelligence network, End of life care profiles
